Class Raytracer.Vector3Parameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • Raytracer.ParameterControl
      • Raytracer.Vector3Parameter
  • Enclosing class:
    Raytracer

    public class Raytracer.Vector3Parameter
extends Raytracer.ParameterControl
    A dynamically generated GUI control that controls a Vector3 value. This is built out of 3 FloatParameters, one for each component of the vector.

      • Vector3Parameter

        Vector3Parameter​(java.lang.Object obj,
                 java.lang.String fieldName,
                 java.lang.String labelText,
                 Raytracer.Vector3 initialValue)
        Creates a Vector3Parameter with no sliders.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object that contains the field to be controlled.
        fieldName - the name of the field on the object that this should control. Should be of type Vector3.
        labelText - the text displayed beside the control.
        initialValue - the initial value of the control. The initial values of each FloatParameter will be set to the components of this vector.

      • Vector3Parameter

        Vector3Parameter​(java.lang.Object obj,
                 java.lang.String fieldName,
                 java.lang.String labelText,
                 Raytracer.Vector3 initialValue,
                 float minValue,
                 float maxValue)
        Creates a Vector3Parameter with sliders.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object that contains the field to be controlled.
        fieldName - the name of the field on the object that this should control. Should be of type Vector3.
        labelText - the text displayed beside the control.
        initialValue - the initial value of the control. The initial values of each FloatParameter will be set to the components of this vector.
        minValue - the lower bound of each slider.
        maxValue - the upper bound of each slider.

      • Vector3Parameter

        Vector3Parameter​(java.lang.Object obj,
                 java.lang.String fieldName,
                 java.lang.String labelText,
                 Raytracer.Vector3 initialValue,
                 boolean isColor)
        Creates a Vector3Parameter that controls an RGB color. The range of the slider will be set to 0-255, but the value passed on will be in the range 0-1 to stay consistent with color vectors elsewhere in the program.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object that contains the field to be controlled.
        fieldName - the name of the field on the object that this should control. Should be of type Vector3.
        labelText - the text displayed beside the control.
        initialValue - the initial value of the control. The initial values of each FloatParameter will be set to the components of this vector.
        isColor - set to true to indicate that this is a color vector.
